From the Infowars web site ::

Alex talks with former sheriff Richard Mack today in-studio. Mack served in the Provo, Utah, police department and was named Elected Official of the Year by the Arizona-New Mexico Coalition of Counties in 1994. He is renowned for challenging the constitutionality of the Brady Bill and fought it all the way to the United States Supreme Court where Mack and other police officers won a monumental decision for freedom. Mack and Alex will talk about Fast and Furious, the federal government operation to smuggle weapons into Mexico.

Today's broadcast goes 30 minutes into a 4th hour.
